The new adaptation of 'The Lion King' opens in cinemas in just two weeks' time. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - South African composer and producer Lebo M has collaborated with Beyoncé on a new song for The Lion King film. The new adaptation of the film opens in cinemas in just two weeks' time. It has been 25 years since the original movie was released. WATCH: New 'Lion King' trailer features Scar, Timon and Pumba Lebo M says the song was recorded in separate studios but is certain to be a major hit. “We are very excited about the song. I can be ambitious and say that I have a feeling that song might just be bigger than Circle of Life, so we are very excited,” Lebo M said. The film will be in cinemas on 19 July and feature the voices of Donald Glover, Seth Rogen, Chiwetel Ejiofor, Alfre Woodard, Billy Eichner, John Kani, John Oliver, Beyoncé Knowles-Carter, and James Earl Jones.